album.title: Euphoria (Original Score from the HBO Series)

wiki.summary: “When I R.I.P” is a track from Euphoria’s Original Score by Labrinth and is featured in multiple episodes of the show. It uses a wide range of quirky language, delving into teenager-related topics such as social media, substance usage, street life and being constantly on the move. It seems as the person whom Labrinth is singing about, whom he sometimes refers to in the first person, is a gun-toting hustler, someone that is not afraid to get into fights and pursue a dangerous lifestyle in general. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: “When I R.I.P” is a track from Euphoria’s Original Score by Labrinth and is featured in multiple episodes of the show. It uses a wide range of quirky language, delving into teenager-related topics such as social media, substance usage, street life and being constantly on the move. It seems as the person whom Labrinth is singing about, whom he sometimes refers to in the first person, is a gun-toting hustler, someone that is not afraid to get into fights and pursue a dangerous lifestyle in general. This perfectly describes a lot of characters from the show, but mostly the main one, in particular, Rue. That track is first heard in the pilot when the show’s protagonist, Rue (Zendaya), describes her descent into drug addiction and the feeling she gets when she is high. Read more on Last.fm.
